<PERSON> Williams </PERSON> said winning passage of a law requiring employers to give 60 days advance notice of plant closings and layoffs has renewed labor's confidence going into the campaign's final 11 weeks. `` In the primaries, we had our members running -LRB- as potential delegates to national conventions -RRB- on behalf of every <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> candidate, but we have a very united position now in the <ORGANIZATION> Steel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Workers </ORGANIZATION>, and my sense is it's that way across the labor movement,'' <PERSON> Williams </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Owen </PERSON> <PERSON> Bieber </PERSON>, the president of the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Auto </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Workers </ORGANIZATION>, said a poll of his members by the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Arbitration </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> showed a 96.9 percent level of support for <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>. `` And that was before <PERSON> Dan </PERSON> <PERSON> Quayle </PERSON>,'' <PERSON> Bieber </PERSON> said, referring to the <LOCATION> Indiana </LOCATION> senator tapped last week as the <ORGANIZATION> GOP </ORGANIZATION> vice presidential nominee and the controversy since then on his use of family connections to help him avoid the Vietnam War draft. <PERSON> Quayle </PERSON> led the <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> administration's opposition on <LOCATION> Capitol </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hill </LOCATION> to the plant closing notices law and has one of the lowest pro-labor voting records _ 9 percent _ in the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION>. Labor leaders acknowledged that an overwhelming majority of their rank-and-file probably are unaware of <PERSON> Quayle </PERSON>'s role in defeating union-sought labor legislation over the past seven years. One of their missions between now and Election Day, they said, is to educate their members on <PERSON> Quayle </PERSON>'s