<HEAD>Coast Guard Says Barge Has Stopped Leaking Fuel</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KILMARNOCK, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A petroleum barge that sprang a leak after possibly being damaged in a storm has stopped spewing fuel, and an 18-square-mile slick wo n't do serious environmental damage to the <LOCATION> Chesapeake </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bay </LOCATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> says. `` While she's been aground, she's lost effectively all of her cargo from two tanks,'' said Cmdr. <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Naccara </PERSON>, executive officer of the <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION>'s Marine Safety office in <LOCATION> Hampton </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Roads </LOCATION>. The vessel, which leaked about 4,000 barrels, or 168,000 gallons, of light fuel, remained in containment booms set up Wednesday afternoon, <PERSON> Naccara </PERSON> said late Wednesday. The 240-foot barge ran aground Wednesday morning in about 12 feet of water in Indian <LOCATION> Creek </LOCATION> on the <LOCATION> Chesapeake </LOCATION>'s western shore. The <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> diverted the barge into the creek in an attempt to get it to a pier where it could unload the fuel. The barge held 19,500 barrels of diesel fuel and gasoline, <PERSON> Naccara </PERSON> said. `` We had a three-mile-by-six-mile sheen,'' said <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> Lt. <PERSON> Rod </PERSON> <PERSON> Walker </PERSON>. `` It will disperse over time.'' <PERSON> Mike </PERSON> <PERSON> LaCivida </PERSON>, a spokesman for the <ORGANIZATION> Virginia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Emergency </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION>, said some of the fuel washed ashore. The <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> said it expected minimal to moderate environmental damage. `` It's such a light oil that dissipates and evaporate