<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A gunman in a car opened fire on a crowd outside a pool hall, wounding eight people in a gang-related shooting, police said today. No arrests were made, and nobody could provide a description of the assailant's vehicle, police officer <PERSON> Ralph </PERSON> <PERSON> Askew </PERSON> said. The victims were standing outside a pool hall in south central <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> late Wednesday when 18 to 19 rounds, possibly from an automatic weapon such as an AK-47 assault rifle, were fired from the vehicle, <PERSON> Askew </PERSON> said. The area is popular with drug dealers, police said. Wednesday night's attack apparently was in revenge for a shooting of a rival gang member earlier this week, <PERSON> Askew </PERSON> said. He was unable to provide any details of the previous shooting. It was believed to be the worst multiple shooting since the so-called Good Friday drive-by shooting earlier this year, in which 13 people were hit, one fatally. In addition to the eight wounded, a pregnant woman was hurt during the panic, <PERSON> Askew </PERSON> said. She was taken to <ORGANIZATION> California </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Medical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> after complaining of labor pains, but birth was not imminent and doctors were trying to stabilize her condition, said hospital administrator <PERSON> Marlene </PERSON> <PERSON> Delp </PERSON>. Another woman, who was shot in the leg, was in good condition at the hospital, Ms. <PERSON> Delp </PERSON> said. Six other victims were treated and released at two other hospitals, but authorities could not specify the condition of the ninth victim.
