 A decision on whether to deploy a full or partial Star Wars defense system must await more research into its capabilities and costs, Republican <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> said in a published interview. `` We do n't know yet, which system is going to be the most effective, so my view is full funding of the research and then make the deployment decision when you have all the cards on the table,'' <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> said in an interview published in Friday's editions of <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times </ORGANIZATION>. The vice president, in an apparent softening of earlier promises to deploy the Strategic Defense Initiative `` as soon as feasible,'' indicated that cost would be a factor in determining whether to deploy it. President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> has advanced SDI _ an anti-missile system using new, space-based technologies _ as a shield against nuclear missiles which could make those weapons obsolete. `` I do n't think we yet know what the price tag will be,'' <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> said. `` If you went to a full deployment of a full strategic defense, it would be very expensive. What I want to do is to continue reserach at the levels of funding, essentially, that we have requested.'' The <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> administration has asked for more than $ 4 billion for SDI research this year. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> also said that he recently has become interested in the concept of a limited system _ `` not a full shield, but a partial deployment.'' `` If I can get convinced by the experts that that would be a guardian, a safeguard against a weapon accidentally fired, or weapons in the hands of some terrorist state, then I'd be interested in this partial deployment,'' he said. `` At this juncture I am not prepared to endorse it, but I'm not prepared to totally reject it,'' <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> added. The Times said the interview was conducted as <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> flew to <LOCATION> Houston </LOCATION> after a rally in <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> on Wednesday. In <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>'s speech accepting the Republican nomination for president last week, he said he would `` continue our policy of peace through strength,'' and added: `` I will modernize and preserve our technological edge and that includes strategic defense.'' A passage in the <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> platform reads, `` We are committed to rapid and certain deployment of SDI as technologies permit ...''
