if any changes for 1989, the 50th anniversary of the Mercury name. Production of Thunderbird and Cougar is to begin in October. The cars will be on introduced to the public Dec. 26 _ both late starts for a new model year, which officially begins Oct. 1. <ORGANIZATION> Lincoln-Mercury </ORGANIZATION> is targeting total sales of 717,000 cars next year, a 7 percent market share of a projected 10.25 million car sales. That would be an increase of 0.3 percentage points over this year and give the division its best year since 1978.
