with closing stock price. Picks up 4th graf pvs, Two weeks ...</NOTE>
<DATELINE>MERIDEN, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Insilco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> said Thursday it accepted a $ 1.1 billion buyout offer from two <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> oilmen, tossing aside a previous takeover agreement with a management-led group. Under the latest arrangement, <ORGANIZATION> INR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Holdings </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, headed by <PERSON> Cyril </PERSON> <PERSON> Wagner </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON> and <PERSON> Jack </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Midland </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, will pay $ 31.75 in cash for each of <ORGANIZATION> Insilco </ORGANIZATION>'s outstanding 25.6 million shares. Including debt, the deal has an indicated value of about $ 1.1 billion, <ORGANIZATION> Insilco </ORGANIZATION> said in a statement. In active trading on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Insilco </ORGANIZATION> closed up $ 1.12 -LCB- a share Thursday to $ 31.12 -LCB-. Two weeks ago, <ORGANIZATION> Insilco </ORGANIZATION> agreed to a management-led leveraged buyout with <ORGANIZATION> First </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Boston </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp </ORGANIZATION>. But <ORGANIZATION> Insilco </ORGANIZATION>'s board said Thursday that it had withdrawn its support of the $ 29-a-share offer, which valued the company at about $ 950 million. <ORGANIZATION> Dissenting </ORGANIZATION> shareholders last week filed lawsuits against <ORGANIZATION> Insilco </ORGANIZATION>, charging that management's offer was too low. In a leveraged buyout a company is acquired largely through borrowed funds that are repaid through the target company's profits or asset sales. Anaylysts had said higher bids would increase the chance a buyer would have to sell at least some divisions of <ORGANIZATION> Insilco </ORGANIZATION> to finance the purchase. Once a leading silver operation known as <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Silver </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Insilco </ORGANIZATION> restructured itself into an industrial holding company and producer of specialty consumer and high technology products. Several subsidiaries have wide brand-name recognition, including Rolodex desktop equipment, <ORGANIZATION> Red </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Devil </ORGANIZATION> paints and <PERSON> Taylor </PERSON> school yearbooks. <ORGANIZATION> Insilco </ORGANIZATION> reported a flat overall earnings for the first half of 1988, $ 21.7 million, or $ 1.02 a share, vs. $ 21.5 million, or $ 1.02, a year ago. But its profit from ongoing operations increased about 11 percent and sales rose almost 21 percent. <PERSON> Wagner </PERSON> and <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> are engaged in the exploration and production of oil and natural gas, the operation of gas pipelines, real estate development and other businesses. Earlier this year, the pair launched a hostile tender offer for <ORGANIZATION> USG </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, a Chicago-based building products concern. But <PERSON> Wagner </PERSON> and <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> terminated their offer in June, a month after they lost a bid for six seats on <ORGANIZATION> USG </ORGANIZATION>'s board in a heated proxy contest. To finance the <ORGANIZATION> Insilco </ORGANIZATION> acquisition, <ORGANIZATION> INR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Holdings </ORGANIZATION> said it has obtained commitments totaling $ 980 million from <LOCATION> Wagner </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> Merrill </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lynch </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Co. The deal received the unanimous endorsement of a special committee of outside directors, <ORGANIZATION> Insilco </ORGANIZATION> said. <ORGANIZATION> INR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Holdings </ORGANIZATION> will begin a cash tender offer within five business days of the execution of a definitive merger agreement.
