 on special savings accounts, called Super NOW accounts, was unchanged at 5.13 percent. Bank Rate Monitor said the effective annual yield was 7.58 percent on six-month certificates of deposit, up from 7.51 the previous week. Yields were 7.89 percent on 1-year CDs, up from 7.82 percent; 8.18 percent on 2 -LCB- - year CDs, up from 8.12 percent; and 8.50 percent on 5-year CDs, up from 8.45 percent
